Installation Methods:

To Deploy an openshift cluster ,administrators must use the openshift-install binary.
This command is also know an the openshift-installer
The main assests generated by the Openshift-install are the ignition configuration files for the bootstrap ,control plane node and compute nodes.
With these 3 ignition config files and the underlying infrastrucute correctly configured ,adminstrators can start an openshift Container platform cluster installation.

Ignition is the first boot provisioning tool designed to configure the RHCOS systems early in the boot process.
It uses the ignition files (Json formated to declare the desired state of the RHCOS system.
The ignition process applies the required configuration during the first boot of the RHCOS system to enforce the desired state of the system.
The ignition process is based on the:
-> Based on the Standard Linux boot process.
-> Runs on the physical nodes ,virtual nodes , cloud instances.
-> Unifies Kick-start and the cloud-init features on the RHCOS system boot.
-> Is executed in the initramfs step of the RHCOS boot process.
-> Configure storage,systemd units,certificates, users,and custom configuration on the RHCOS when they first boot.
-> Consumes the ignition configuration files generated with the openshift-install command and the machine config operator(MCO).
     -> The openshift-install command uses the ignition configuration files to set the exact state of the each node upon installation.
	 -> The machine config operator applies the other changes to the nodes after installation,such as applying new certificates or ssh keys.
	 
The ignition process loads the configuration files from one of the following locations:
> Local disk
> Cloud metadata
> Over the network usig the http or https

	 
 